reviewText:
This is unique game with non-target system. To feel how it work you need to try it. No, you MUST try it, cause:
- awesome graphics (CryEngine 3 - sounds good, eh?);
- nice battle mechanics;
- 8 classes;
- lots of maps and game modes;
- cool in-game atmosphere.

Go on, try Panzar!

I'm a veteran of this game from before it was released on Steam. Most of the negative reviews for this game are coming from people who have only played the game on steam and have under an hour on record, not exactly people who's opinion I would trust.

Now for the actual review: The good;

+The game looks visually stunning, it's running on the Cryengine and is one of the most graphically pleasing and atmospheric games available. The terrain and characters are flawlessly animated, the models are excellently rendered and the particle effects are magnificent. However the more technologically minded among you may be wondering if it looks so good it must have hardware limitations and optimisation issues". Well

